{{Quote|Vildar, this is ''Adept Tarna Miak'', the Sorcerers of Tund's representative in the Convocation.|[[Matthea Cathley]], introducing Tarna Miak to [[Vildar Mac]]|<ref name="The High Republic 1">[[The High Republic (2022) 1|''The High Republic'' (2022) 1]]</ref>}}
[[File:ConvocationChambers-PeaceAndUnity.png|thumb|right|350px|[[Convocation of the Force]] representatives]]
'''Representative''' was a title held by individuals who represented [[religion]]s on the [[Convocation of the Force]].<ref name="The High Republic 1" /> In [[382 BBY]],<ref name="Date note">{{PeaceandUnityDate}}</ref> [[Kilan T'Dara]] served as the [[Church of the Force]]' representative and the Convocation's [[Chairman|chair]],<ref name="The High Republic 4">[[The High Republic (2022) 4|''The High Republic'' (2022) 4]]</ref> [[Leebon]] served as the [[Jedi Order]]'s representative,<ref name="The High Republic 1" /> [[Elris Florent]] served as the [[Disciples of the Whills]]' representative, [[Sirené]] served as the [[Fallanassi]]'s representative, [[Waran Val]] served as the [[Matukai]]'s representative<ref name="Peace and Unity">{{StoryCite|story=Peace and Unity|book=The High Republic (2022) 1}}</ref> and [[Tarna Miak]] served as the [[Sorcerers of Tund]]'s representative.<ref name="The High Republic 1" /> The title was also used in the [[Naboo planetary legislative assembly]].<ref name="Queen's Shadow">''[[Queen's Shadow]]''</ref>

